<br>
-GUI - almost identical to diablo isoview UI with more options, I thought the ui is going to take a long time to get used to. But to my surprise it's actually very well done and almost same as diablo, after 1 hr into the game it became second nature. This is probably a good thing when you start pvping. To all the people hating the UI..hmmm?<br>
<br>
- There are pockets of Lag, not much worse than a bad night in EQ though. Not a big problem.<br>
<br>
- Graphics - Daoc quality, however I didnt try the high settings, they slowed my machine to a 5 fps avg. I have a geforce3 ti500, 700+ ddr 1.4 athlon xp machine. Overall the graphic is not eq2, but it's decent and designed to work with 200+ players in big battles.<br>
<br>
- The amount of class/skill customization in this game is mind boggling. You can start with a base class, at level 10 specialize into another one, then a bit later further speicalize into another set of classes(i havent figured it all yet). For example my path is probably going to be rogue(class set 1)-&gt;assassin(set2)-&gt;blackhand(set3).  On top of all that, you can also pick perks when you make your character much like morrowwind/daggerfall. For example, perk raised by thieves, will give +5 to dagger etc. <br>
<br>
-THERE IS BLOOD IN THE GAME!! OMG RUN FOR YA LIVES<br>
<br>
It exceeded my initial expectation, and I am sure once I get pass the newbie levels, town siege and guild battles will be a lot of fun. <br>
<br>
gaga, gnome<br>
p.s. if you absolutely hate pvp then dont bother. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gagaliya>gagaliya</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/~gagaliya/sharpteeth.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/28/03 5:41:36 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=infotainmentx>Infotainmentx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 800<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/28/03 12:52:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25555.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: shadowbane</span><hr size=1> I've never played the game, but I've seen it played.<br>
